🌟 Savannah is such an amazing city with so much rich history and even better for seen . Two must try spots are @ordinarypub and @commonrestraunt !
✨ The Ordinary Pub was such a great experience from the moment you walk in. The entrance is to the old basement of Savannah’s original Sears & Roebuck building. You literally have to walk down stairs to get to this amazing and spacious gastropub with an amazing ambiance with 200-year-old back walls and stained glass. The we started with the savory donut sliders which were delicious . Both entrees the steak and eggs as well as the Mac & cheese were delicious. The Mac and cheese was very creamy and cheesy with great flavor, be sure to come hungry because it s hearty. The steak was cooked to to the perfect temperature and the combination of the chimmichurri sauce really elevated the dish. Oh and what brunch would be complete without bottomless mimosas 🥂 😜. There is also a secret door that leads to another beautiful bar that offers a spacious venue to rent for your next event! 
⭐️ Be sure to ask for Carly when you visit, our mimosas were never empty and her positive energy and knowledge of the menu were exceptional.
